{"queries": ["What territorial entity does the town where John the Hairy lived belong to?", ""John the Hairy location"", ""John the Hairy Rostov""], "passages": [["Romenskyi Raion () is a raion in Sumy Oblast in Central Ukraine. The administrative center of the raion is the town of Romny, which is administratively incorporated as a city of oblast significance and does not belong to the raion. Population:", "Pavlohrad Raion () is a raion (district) of Dnipropetrovsk Oblast, southeastern-central Ukraine. Its administrative centre is located at Pavlohrad, which is separately incorporated as a town of oblast significance and does not belong to the district. Population: .", "Kaniv Raion is a raion (district) of Cherkasy Oblast, central Ukraine. Its administrative centre is located at the town of Kaniv which is incorporated separately as a city of oblast significance and does not belong to the raion. Population:", "Khmilnyk Raion () is one of the 33 regions of Vinnytsia Oblast, located in southwestern Ukraine. The administrative center of the raion is the city of Khmilnyk, which does not belong to the district and is incorporated separately as a town of oblast significance. Population:", "El Chupadero is a town in the municipality of Santa Rita, Chalatenango, El Salvador. Currently the town is used for agricultural purposes, but it does have houses in which people live. There are two main roads in El Chupadero, the first one leads to the town of Santa Rita, and the second leads to the other little town called Los Marines. The land where El Chupadero is located, is home to Enrique Lopez that was elected mayor for Santa Rita for multiple times."], ["Blessed John the Hairy (, also known as John the Merciful of Rostov) was a holy fool (Yurodivy), of the Russian Orthodox Church in the second half of the 16th century. He endured a great many trials in his lifetime. "He did not have a permanent shelter, and at times took his rest at the house of his spiritual Father, a priest at